comments: Williamson (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as body contact occurs with Mitchell (UTA) during his driving shot attempt.
Conley (UTA) makes marginal contact with Williamson's (NOP) body during his drive before dislodging the ball.
Conley (UTA) makes incidental contact with Ball (NOP) as he goes for the loose ball.
Williamson (NOP) makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm and contact affects his pass attempt.
Mitchell (UTA) moves laterally in Adams' (NOP) path at the start of his drive and contact affects his SQBR.
Conley (UTA) is standing inside the three-point arc before Adams (NOP) releases the free throw.
Ball (NOP) briefly places his arm to Mitchells' (UTA) side and quickly removes it defending his drive to the basket.
Ball (NOP) makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm and contact affects his driving shot attempt.
O'Neale (UTA) and Ingram (NOP) engage and disengage off ball.
Gobert (UTA) fully exits the lane at the 1:08 mark and when he steps back into the lane, he is imminently exiting within three seconds.
Gobert (UTA) places his left arm against Williamson (NOP) and then collapses it against his own body and marginal contact occurs.
Adams (NOP) steps out of bounds as he gathers the loose ball.
Ingram (NOP) and Gobert (UTA) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
O'Neale (UTA) moves alongside of Ingram's (NOP) path and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) briefly places his hand to Williamson's (NOP) shoulder and disengages as they pursue the loose ball.
Ball (NOP) briefly places his hand on Mitchell's (UTA) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Mitchell gathers and attempts the shot.
Williamson (NOP) makes incidental contact with Gobert's (UTA) arm as the two players go for the rebound.
Gobert (UTA) jumps into Williamson (NOP) and moves through his space, affecting his ability to get to the rebound.
Bledsoe (NOP) remains in a legal guarding position and marginal contact is created by Conley (UTA) when he jumps to the side as he attempts the jump shot.
Gobert (UTA) makes marginal contact Williamson's (NOP) backside and disengages as they pursue the loose ball.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Hart's (NOP) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.

Mitchell (UTA) is drifting away from Ball (NOP), who stops short and does not move through Mitchell's space during his jump shot attempt.  Marginal contact is created by Mitchell slightly extending his leg towards Ball.
